[src:nonparametric-tests/kendall-rank-correlation-coefficient] We perform this by repeated affine transforms.
[src:nonparametric-tests/kendall-rank-correlation-coefficient] First normalize ${\textstyle X,Y}$ by subtracting the mean and dividing the standard deviation.
[src:nonparametric-tests/kendall-rank-correlation-coefficient] This does not change ${\textstyle \tau _{A}}$ .
[src:nonparametric-tests/kendall-rank-correlation-coefficient] This gives us ${\begin{bmatrix}x\\y\end{bmatrix}}={\begin{bmatrix}1&r\\r&1\end{bmatrix}}^{1/2}{\begin{bmatrix}z\\w\end{bmatrix}}$ where ${\textstyle (Z,W)}$ is sampled from the standard normal distribution on ${\textstyle \mathbb {R} ^{2}}$ .
